choices: ^Choices; there are pretty much only two choice types, namely one with the text being output into the story and the other one that hides it.
^Below this you can find the option where it will output the text.

g-0: ^And the following choice doesn't output the text and instead hides it all together

c-1: ^See; no "Hello back!" other than the one that is here.
^To those two choices come a special one. The star indicate only a one time choice that will disapear after one use. If you want to reuse choices however, you need to use the plus symbol.
^Then there is something which you should notice in the text between the choices.
^There is a minus symbol. It indicates to the software that the two different choices need to be seperate otherwise they would appear both at once.
^PLEASE NOTE: Due to the nature of the code if you want to re-read this part please use the arrows in the top right corner to reset the story.

css: ^How to implement a CSS class into the style.css and into the ink files.
^That way you can design them anyway you want as long as they adhere to the CSS rules.
^To find example ones that are already working go to the 3 bars and choose the stylesheet file
^If you want to you can even check out the styles that I already made for older stories.
tags: ^There are certain things called tags which allow you to change a few important things like the theme and the name of the author.
^To change them head to the top of you ink main file and look at this section.
^Easiest is to just change the name of the author and leave dark mode on so you dont get eye problems.
variablesandif: ^To make variables you first have to define them by declaring a var with a specific number.
^The next part is only available in the editor!
^They can then be used to make if clauses to activate choices or chapters etc.
^See, if test wasn't 1 then you would get false.
^You can even get the numver of a variable by displaying it with the following function.
^This was the simple variables tutorial you can either head over to the advanced one or you can head back.

symbols: ^These are available UNICODE Symbols which might come in handy. BEWARE: They mess with the cursor.
^Anything between U+1F550 - U+1F567 for clocks displaying various times
^Anything between U+1F5E8 - U+1F5F1 for displaying speech bubbles
^Anything between U+1D300 - U+1D356 for displaying people
^Anything between U+4DC0 - U+4DFF for displaying people
^Anything between U+1F019U+1F02B (These are majong symbols from 1-9 and a joker for dicerolls maybe)
